body:
### What is the problem this feature will solve?

Avoiding callbacks in [http.request](https://nodejs.org/dist/latest-v18.x/docs/api/http.html#httprequestoptions-callback) module.

``` js 
https.request(options, (res) => {
  // avoid it
})
```

to prove it's a problem for the community, we have many questions in StackOverflow about [Synchronous HTTP requests in Node.js](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/50448635/synchronous-http-requests-in-node-js) and exists a [npm module](https://www.npmjs.com/package/sync-request) only to solve this problem that is used by more than [61k repositories](https://github.com/ForbesLindesay/sync-request/network/dependents?dependent_type=REPOSITORY&package_id=UGFja2FnZS0xNjM5MjQzMQ%3D%3D)

### What is the feature you are proposing to solve the problem?

I would like to create convert the methods to work with promises for `request()` and any function that uses` request()` like `get()` for example
``` js
const http = require('http/promises')
const responseReq = await http.request(options)
const responseGet = await http.get(options)
```

### What alternatives have you considered?

Since it is super focused on async/await problem, I didn't have another solution proposal

