### What is the problem this feature will solve?

It will prevent mutation of arguments/parameters

### What is the feature you are proposing to solve the problem?

I am sure this has been discussed somewhere, curious about this feature:

before:

```
const findRowToSwap = (i, j, m) => {
    for (; i < m.length; i++) {
        if (m[i][j] !== 0) {
            j = 5;  /// we could mutate j here
            return i;
        }
    }
    return -1;
}
```

after

```js
                         // ⌄---------------------- here
const findRowToSwap = (i, const j, m) => {
    for (; i < m.length; i++) {
        if (m[i][j] !== 0) {
           // cannot mutate j anymore
            return i;
        }
    }
    return -1;
}
```

does this exist, is it in the works? would be nice

