You would be able to call the code below,
for example of a method in return instead of the simple this reference object.

```javascript
class Example {
  query() {
    console.log('query');
  }

  static methodOne() {
    return this || this.query();
  }

  static methodTwo() {
    return this || this.query();  // No child method call would feature in the second param, or the call of the method query.
  }
}

Example.methodOne(); // should return the console.log('query');
```

### What is the feature you are proposing to solve the problem?

the feature would be a pull request with the hierarchy class method call change. 

